        <etym xml:lang="ru">Старое сращение преверба %ia-%i с основой %iman-%i (база <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*men-</w></mentioned>); многообразные значения
                последней в индоевропейских языках могут быть объединены общим понятием „проявлять
                духовную активность“; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
                                        ><lang/><w>āmānay-</w><gloss><q>показывать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."
                        /><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><lang/><w>*ni-mānī
                        (nm’ny)</w><gloss><q>раскаяние</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*mān-(m’n-)</w><gloss><q>дух</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                        ><w>*mēn-(myn-)</w><gloss><q>думать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"
                        ><lang/><w>mа́n-</w><gloss><q>думать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>почитать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"
                        ><lang/><w>man-</w><gloss><q>думать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>полагать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>считать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"
                        ><lang/><w>man-</w><gloss><q>считать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/><gloss><q>почитать</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                                ><lang/><w>μιμνήσκω</w><gloss><q>напоминаю</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w>μένος</w><gloss><q>дух</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>mens</w><gloss><q>дух</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w>moneo</w><gloss><q>напоминаю</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>наставляю</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>munan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"
                        ><lang/><w>meinen</w><gloss><q>считать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>полагать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w>mahnen</w><gloss><q>увещевать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>уговаривать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>мнить, по-мнить</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>manyti</w><gloss><q>думать</q></gloss></mentioned> и
                пр. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II
                        264–266</biblScope></bibl>).<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> Значение
                ‘показывать’, ‘учить’ следует рассматривать как каузативное в отношении медиального
                ‘помнить’: следовательно, %iamonyn%i (с исторически долгим %iā%i в основе) —
                „заставлять помнить“ → „учить“; в этом отношении к осетинскому близки <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>monere</w></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                                ><lang/><w>mahnen</w></mentioned>. На какие-то следы „магической“
                семантики этого слова указывает название чудесной чаши в нартовском эпосе:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>Amongæ, Ac-amongæ,
                        Waci-amongæ-</w></mentioned>, ср. также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_amond"
                /> ‘счастье’; может быть, сюда же названия духов: <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wælimon"/>. Чисто эмоциональная семантика основы %iman-%i
                выступает в словах <ref type="xr" target="#entry_monc"/>, д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_mondi"/>; ср. также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_imonaw"/>
                ‘нежный’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæsmon"/> ‘раскаяние’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ævælmon"/> ‘без заботы’.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>172</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">The old contraction of the preverb %ia-%i with the stem %iman-%i (the
                base is <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*men-</w></mentioned>); the various
                meanings of the latter form in Indo-European languages can be united by the general
                concept of ‘showing spiritual activity’; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
                                ><lang/><w>āmānay-</w><gloss><q>show</q></gloss></mentioned>
                                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."
                        /><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><lang/><w>*ni-mānī
                        (nm’ny)</w><gloss><q>remorse</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*mān-(m’n-)</w><gloss><q>spirit</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                        ><w>*mēn-(myn-)</w><gloss><q>think</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"
                        ><lang/><w>mа́n-</w><gloss><q>think</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>respect</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"
                        ><lang/><w>man-</w><gloss><q>think</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>consider</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>regard</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"
                        ><lang/><w>man-</w><gloss><q>consider</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/><gloss><q>respect</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>μιμνήσκω</w><gloss><q>I
                                remind</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                                        ><w>μένος</w><gloss><q>spirit</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>mens</w><gloss><q>spirit</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w>moneo</w><gloss><q>I remind</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>I instruct</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>munan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"
                        ><lang/><w>meinen</w><gloss><q>consider</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>think</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w>mahnen</w><gloss><q>admonish</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>persuade</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>мнить, по-мнить</w></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                        ><lang/><w>manyti</w><gloss><q>think</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.
                                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II
                                264–266</biblScope></bibl>).<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> The
                meaning ‘show’, ‘learn’ should be seen as causative in relation to the middle voice
                ‘remember’: therefore, %iamonyn%i (historically with the long vowel %iā%i in the
                stem) — ‘make remember’ → ‘teach’; in this relation <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                                ><lang/><w>monere</w></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                                ><lang/><w>mahnen</w></mentioned> are close to Ossetic. Some traces
                of the "magical" semantics of this word are indicated by the name of the miraculous
                cup in the Nart epic: <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>Amongæ, Ac-amongæ,
                                Waci-amongæ-</w></mentioned>, cf. also <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_amond"/> ‘happiness’; maybe, the spirit names are also
                related to it: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wælimon"/>. Pure emotional semantics of
                the stem %iman-%i is found in the words <ref type="xr" target="#entry_monc"/>, Digor
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mondi"/>; cf. also <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_imonaw"/> ‘gentle’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæsmon"/>
                ‘remorse’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævælmon"/> ‘careless’.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>172</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
